{
  "stem": "24212.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the Jews were so worried that they couldn't care who the devil is helping them, as long as we were helping them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some of them asked, well, how old are you, deary?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't answer, or we said whatever.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What's you name?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Maria.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You didn't give names away to-- at least not real names, because the next hour they can be captured and interrogated.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And who brought you here?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So and so.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we didn't give names.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Do you recall now the name of the friend who got you involved in the first place?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, yeah, Magda.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's a different Magda.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It just sort happened that it was Magda too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I forget her last name [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[DRINKS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sometimes yes, sometimes no, because many times either there was too much snow or too little snow, whatever, so we stayed on the Hungarian side at some safe house.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But basically, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I'll take your question literally, and then the answer is no.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I found out after the war many, many other things that I didn't know at that time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I-- you could have figured that if we are doing-- saving people or smuggling people across the border in, you know, Poland, Slovakia, Hungary, Yugoslavia, that similar things must have been going on in the west, which they were, also underground railroads on so on.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I teach nowadays, So I know much more today-- much, much more today-- than I knew at that time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was no name.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Czechoslovakia it had to be, yeah.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were so many such lines that-- maybe in France or in Belgium-- I know more today about details and names of the Belgian or French resistance, underground railroad, then I know about the east for a very simple reason.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Much more is written about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
